  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic credibility evidence package for CFD-based absolute hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under VAD operating conditions. Targets W-AR-05 (comparator absence / mismatch): the primary validation result omits a comparedAgainst link, while a secondary result references a comparator dataset drawn from a steady-flow benchtop experiment rather than the pulsatile, physiologically loaded VAD duty cycle declared in the COU. The mismatch is plausibly deniable because the comparator shares pump geometry, working fluid, and four of five operating points with the COU; only the flow waveform character (steady vs. pulsatile) differs, yet that difference is material to shear-history-dependent hemolysis accumulation. The validation narrative frames the comparator favourably without examining its waveform applicability.",
